title: Six South Jersey football picks
text:
Pick: Seneca, 17-14. 
- Delsea (3-0) at Paul VI (3-0): 
The visiting Crusaders will look to control the ball and the clock with their powerful ground game. 
Pick: Delsea, 27-21. 
- Woodstown (2-1) at Pennsville (3-0): 
This Salem County clash of styles features Woodstown's stout defense against Pennsville's high-powered and frenetically-paced offense. 
Pick: Pennsville, 20-17. 
- Hammonton (3-0) at Cherry Hill West (1-2): 
The visiting Blue Devils have a playmaker at quarterback in junior Malachi Winters. 
Pick: Hammonton, 27-20. 
- Oakcrest (2-0) vs. Buena (2-1) at St. Augustine: 
These CAL National rivals played a classic last season, with Buena winning 36-35 in overtime. 
Pick: Buena, 30-27.
